          "kind": "about-group",
          "title": "About the Course",
          "entries": [
            {
              "title": "About the Course",
              "content": "This course includes the following topic(s): Playground Games, Sports, Free Play/ Circuits, Historic Dancing\n\nAbout Playground Games\nPlay group playground games.\n\nAbout Sports\nThis year, students will learn how to play football, badminton, and softball through participating in a variety of games, skills, and activities. Activities are geared for smaller groups of students but can be adjusted to any size.\n\nAbout Free Play/ Circuits\nMake fitness-building routines a habit.\n\nAbout Historic Dancing\nStudents will learn dances that were popular in the historical period being studied and perform them to some music of that period.\n\nPE: Grades 7-12\nLessons specifically created for Grades 7-12. We do recommend you prioritize the Historical Dance lessons as these are less likely to be obtained elsewhere and also give depth and richness to student's understanding of the time period. We recommend you make sure to include some sort of physical activity as breaks throughout your school day. If you already have sports or similar activities as a regular part of your life rhythms, these lessons are optional."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "kind": "tips-group",
          "title": "Placement & Combining Tips",
          "entries": [
            {
              "title": "Placement & Combining Tips",
              "content": "Playground Games\nSuitable for interested younger students.\n\nSports\nMinimal supplies are required.\n\nFree Play/ Circuits\nStudents may also choose to take a local Pilates or Yoga class.\n\nHistoric Dancing\nThis course is suitable for interested students in Grades 5-6 if combining."
            }
          ]
        },
